Bug.WithStack:
CommonBaseEventLogRecrod does not map properties to Common Base Event 
properties correctly.

The LogRecord's sequence number should be mapped to the CBE's sequence number, 
which appears to be a linear mapping.  Also, when filtering and displaying the 
resulting CBEs based on severity, it makes sense to me to map the LogRecord's 
level to the CBE's severity property (as well as setting the level name and 
value as EDEs) using the following mapping:

        if (level.equals(Level.ALL)) {
            return 0;
        }
        else if (level.equals(Level.FINEST)) {
            return 10;
        }
        else if (level.equals(Level.FINER)) {
            return 12;
        }
        else if (level.equals(Level.FINE)) {
            return 14;
        }
        else if (level.equals(Level.CONFIG)) {
            return 16;
        }
        else if (level.equals(Level.INFO)) {
            return 18;
        }
        else if (level.equals(Level.WARNING)) {
            return 30;
        }
        else if (level.equals(Level.SEVERE)) {
            return 50;
        }

        return 70;
	
	Finally, the source class and method names as well as the thread ID 
could all be mapped to the source component ID (component, subcomponet and 
theadId respectively).
Custom levels can be defined with different Level.intValues.  Consider 
comparing based on intValue >= some value.  For example, a DETAIL level which 
is finer than CONFIG, but less fine than FINE, and it might be better to map 
that to 16 than 70.  However, the ranges will be quite large since Java Logging 
uses integer ranges from 300 - 1000 and Integer.MIN_VALUE/Integer.MAX_VALUE for 
ALL/NONE.

After a closer inspection, Java Logging's thread ID is a simple integer counter 
and not the name of the current thread.  As such, this value is not mappable,  
However, the sourceMethodName and sourceClassName are perfect candidates for 
the sourceComponentId's sub/component properties.  Since the goal is to 
generate valid Common Base Events for the use case where an empty 
sourceComponentId exists.  The logger name does not necessarily infer anything 
about the reporter/source of the event but rather the handler of the event 
(e.g. logging facility) which decreases it utility as the sourceComponentId's 
component.   

These mappings are analogous to APIs and should be deprecated for two major 
releases before modifications can be adopted.  Also, only the sourceMethodName 
and sourceClassName are potential candidates for the sourceComponentId's 
sub/component properties and callers may not want this level of granularity for 
their sourceComponentId.  Finally, the current mapping permits LogRecord 
properties to be persisted in the Common Base Event without overwriting 
existing core properties.  As such, to maintain ease of usability (e.g. all 
LogRecord properties are mapped to Extended Data Elements), the current mapping 
will be used.
Closing.

