Bug.WithStack:
Currently, when a packet is received from the target, we check if it's 
corresponding request has timed out by doing this:

 synchronized (fTimedOutPackets) {
            Integer id = new Integer(packet.getId());
            if (fTimedOutPackets.remove(id)) {
                return; // already timed out. No need to keep this one
            }
        }

It would be more efficient to check if the fTimedOutPackets was empty first.
Fixed in PacketReceiveManager.
Please verify, Kevin.
