if you have a source file which contains some classes, first open them in Open Type Hierarchy view, then make some changes in the source file such as move a class in/out from a namespace, save the changes, make sure the indexer kicks in. Try reopen the same class in Hierarchy view from outline view, an error message pops out and NPE is generated as below. And the view becomes unusable. Restart the IDE will solve it.
********************** Error May 09, 2005 16:08:38.10 java.lang.NullPointerException
for you 8-) I'm not sure if some of these features were ever working prior to the indexer migration. Resubmitting to the pool for further assistance from the community. This works in the new type hierarchy (bug 142189)
